{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But finally, once they went to war, everybody-- I did-- practically everybody was convinced that Hitler would be defeated in a short period of time, a month, two or three.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we ran away just to avoid the oncoming onslaught of the Germans, and believing that the Poles sooner or later will manage to group their forces and resist him.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And with the help from the Allies, France and Germany, Hitler will be defeated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We'll be back home in two months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Instead came the big surprise that Stalin-- which nobody knew about, it was a shock to everybody, including to the west-- that Stalin behind the scenes reached an agreement with Hitler and they divided Poland.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that finished that dream up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's 1940-- 1939, 1940, and half of 1941.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father and my brother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we corresponded.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We corresponded.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father opened up another factory on a very small scale, again making tar-paper.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And under the Russians, there was a system where small factories could exist as cooperatives.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he organized sort of like a co-operative like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was semi-nationalized, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a-- an office which managed all these little cooperatives, because private enterprise as such was not allowed, so it was basically cooperatives, you know, nationalized.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we worked in that factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Me and my brother worked in the factory.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father was sort of the technical manager of that factory.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And at one point, the Russians announced that anybody who wants to go back home, meaning for refugees like ourselves who want to go back to their original residence, will be allowed to do though-- to do so.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He has to register.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Approximately nearly close to a million refugees who ran away from Poland like ourselves, mostly Jews, were in that same situation.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
